   of “The Talented 12,” a group of young, rising stars in chemistry.
   Read more

27/08/2018 Joseph Moran Named “Talented Twelve”

The Foundation
02/10/2018 Scholarships for Master’s degrees in Chemistry

   Thanks to the generosity of former students of the university,
   researchers and businesses, every year, the Foundation awards grants to
   support high-achieving students at the start of their master’s degree.
   The means-tested grants are awarded to excellent candidates and
   applications can be renewed to continue into the second year, for an
   amount of up to 5000 euros.
   Read more

02/10/2018 Scholarships for Master’s degrees in Chemistry

